UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407692901136
AB  - Score tests of extra-Poisson variation in left- or right-truncated Poisson regression models are derived for alternatives in the left- or right-truncated negative binomial family and for arbitrary truncation points. Using asymptotic expansions of the score function, adjustment factors are derived for the tests which are expected to improve their small sample properties. Overdispersion tests for the untruncated Poisson model in the econometric and statistical literature are special cases of the tests derived in this paper. A Monte Carlo investigation of the new tests when data are truncated at zero show that the effect of truncation produces a significant size distortion and power reduction, especially in small samples, but also that the corrections suggested by asymptotic expansions improve the performance of the tests.
